    1. What is the main difference between Power BI Desktop downloaded from the Microsoft Store or from the web?

      Power BI Desktop downloaded from the web will automatically stay updated while Power BI Desktop downloaded from the Microsoft Store needs to be manually updated.

      Power BI Desktop downloaded from the Microsoft Store will automatically stay updated while Power BI Desktop downloaded from the web needs to be manually updated.

      There is no difference between Power BI Desktop downloaded from the Microsoft Store and Power BI Desktop downloaded from the web, both will automatically stay updated.

      There is no difference between Power BI Desktop downloaded from the Microsoft Store and Power BI Desktop downloaded from the web, both need to be manually updated.


    2. Which of the following can’t be done with the Setup Reporting Data wizard?

      Create a new data set

      Create a new query or page

      Create a copy of an existing data set

      Edit an existing data set


    3. How do you need to publish your pages and queries as web services so that Power BI Desktop can access them?

      You need to add a web service collection to the extension. The web service collection then needs a web service entry for every object you want to publish as a web service.

      You need to add a web service to the extension. The web service then needs a web service entry for every object you want to publish as a web service.

      You need to navigate to the web services pages in Business Central and add the queries and pages as web services, after you have published and installed your extension.

      You need to upload a webservicecollection.xml file to your Business Central instance. The webservicecollection.xml needs a web service entry for every object you want to publish as a web service.


    4. What is the purpose of the DataAccessIntent property?

      The DataAccessIntent property sets whether to get data for the object from a read-only replica of the database or the primary database.

      The DataAccessIntent property sets whether to get data for the object from a backup of the database or the primary database.

      The DataAccessIntent property sets whether to get data for the object from a data warehouse created of the primary database.

      The DataAccessIntent property sets whether to get data for the object from memory or from the data files, used for the primary database.
